9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 366, L.D. 834, “An Act to Update the
10 State Supplement to Supplemental Security Income”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §3271, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 405, Pt. A, §65, is
14 further amended to read:
15 2. The department, to the extent allowed by Title XVI of the United States Social
16 Security Act, as amended, and regulations promulgated thereunder, shall establish standard
17 levels of state supplemental income benefits for blind, disabled and elderly people. The
18 benefits must be provided under a modified flat benefit system, and may vary by marital
19 status, and by living arrangements to the extent allowed by Title XVI of the United States
20 Social Security Act, as amended, and regulations promulgated thereunder. The benefits
21 may not be based on individual budgeted need and may not vary by category or
22 geographical area. Benefits for a couple, except as provided under section 3273, subsection
23 1, paragraph B, must be equal to the sum of the amount of benefit for an each individual
24 and 50% of the benefit for an individual in the couple.
25 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §3272, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 1973, c. 790, §3, is amended to
26 read:
27 1. Standard. The standard utilized to determine need shall must be the current annual
28 budget at the lower level of living for a retired couple an individual as most recently
29 determined by the United States Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics, for
30 Portland, Maine, or budgets which that are consistent with such a budget at the lower level
31 of living, taking into account budget variances by marital status and living arrangements
32 permited permitted pursuant to Title XVI of the United States Social Security Act, as
33 amended, and regulations promulgated thereunder.
34 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §3273, sub-§1, as amended by PL 1985, c. 770, §3, is further
35 amended to read:
