1 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
2 allocations are made.
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
4 State Supplement to Federal Supplemental Security Income 0131
5 Initiative: Provides funding to increase the minimum state supplemental income benefit for
6 recipients of federal supplemental security income from $8 per month to $65 per month for
7 an individual and to increase the combined state supplemental benefit for a couple, each of
8 whom qualify for the benefit, from 150% to 200% of the benefit for an individual.
9 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
10 All Other $23,135,664 $23,135,664
11 __________ __________
12 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $23,135,664 $23,135,664
139 '
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment does the following.
18 1. It replaces provisions of law that currently provide that payments to couples, both
19 of whom receive the supplement, are 150% of the benefit for an individual with provisions
20 of law providing that payments to the couples are 200% of the benefit for an individual.
21 2. It requires that the standard used to determine need is the current annual budget at
22 the lower level of living for an individual as most recently determined by the United States
23 Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics, for Portland, Maine, or budgets consistent
24 with such a budget taking into account budget variances by living arrangements permitted
25 pursuant to Title XVI of the United States Social Security Act.
26 3. It establishes that, in determining any increase according to the United States
27 Consumer Price Index, consideration must be given to the goal of reaching, within a
28 reasonable time, a benefit level equal to or consistent with the current budget at the lower
29 level of living for an individual, rather than a retired couple, established by the United
30 States Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics, for Portland, Maine.
